                  <persName id="t18180114-185-person1269">
                  JOHN 
                  ALLEN
               <interp inst="t18180114-185-person1269" type="surname" value="ALLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-185-person1269" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180114-185-person1269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an ironmonger, and live in High-street, Marylebone, opposite Mr. Padmore's; I saw three men standing by his door, the prisoner was one of them. One of them 
               <persName id="t18180114-185-person1270">drew</persName>
             the cloth out of the pile, which was inside the door - They had all three been talking together, and all three ran away together; I pursued, the linen dropped from one of them. I seized the prisoner, the others got away. I never lost sight of him. I am sure he was one of them.</p>
               <p>GEORGE PADMORE. I am a linen-draper, and live opposite Mr. Allen's. The rope that fastened the pile was cut.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I know nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
